{
  "texts": [
    "This task diverged from the previous ones in that no labeled training data was supplied to participants, meaning that participants could not evaluate the quality of their models' predictions until test time.",
    "The objective task was to assess a user's level of eating disorder severity through analysis of their Reddit posting history.",
    "Given the composition of both the eRisk lab and the SMHD dataset (50) predominantly with social media data, it is notable that an overwhelming majority (93%) of the studies in our analysis employ this data type.",
    "This underscores the widespread reliance on social media sources in modern research methodologies.",
    "This finding confirms the results of Zhang et al."
  ]
}